Frontend overhaul: sidebar nav, bug fixes, theme consistency, and backend improvements

Frontend:
- Replace horizontal Navbar with collapsible Sidebar (desktop + mobile drawer)
- Add 5 grouped nav sections (Main, Analysis, Operations, Platform, Account)
- Wire missing routes: /benchmarks, /pcaf, /reviews, /recommendations
- Fix crash in reports/[id] export (undefined setError to exportError state)
- Fix crash in scenarios page (removed nonexistent fetchData call)
- Standardize theme colors in PCAF, Reviews, MFA pages (CSS variables)
- Add Web Vitals telemetry hook with sendBeacon reporting
- Add env validation, robots.ts, sitemap.ts, OG/Twitter meta, JSON-LD
- Add .env.production.example and .env.staging.example
- Raise coverage thresholds (80/70/70/80)
- Update Sidebar tests (8 tests covering sections, routes, user info, logout)

Backend and Subnet:
- Add per-miner circuit breakers and median-based consensus in subnet bridge
- Add adaptive EMA alpha with cold-start scoring in validator
- Add dynamic miner skipping for consecutive zero scorers
- Add protocol versioning (v2) with hash prefix in CarbonSynapse
- Add dual scoring weights (with/without ground truth)
- Tighten overconfidence penalty and benchmark tolerance
- Add breakdown-to-scope transitive consistency checks in GHG compliance
- Add TTL + SHA-256 cache for emission factor datasets
- Add API deprecation middleware (Sunset/Deprecation headers)
- Add 4 new curated test cases (financial services, zero-emission, mega-corp, construction)
- Support vehicle_type field in miner and ground truth computation
- Normalize scope3 materiality weights
- Use LRU eviction for miner rate limiter
- Configurable validator/miner scripts (interval, timeout, alpha, rate limits)

DevOps:
- Add K8s manifest validation job in CI
- Use __IMAGE_TAG__ placeholder in K8s backend/frontend deployments
- Fix Trivy action version (0.28.0 to 0.24.0)
